What is resilience?

The key to resilience is getting on top of things early. Be mindful and learn to recognise the signs and your own personal triggers.

Your Triggers

Understanding your personal triggers - recognising what 'pushes your buttons', and knowing your limitations.

Your Experiences

The impacts of past experiences - if they've been properly handled and learned from, past experiences can boost resilience. If not, they can increase stress and decrease your ability to cope.

Your Emotions

Handling emotional change - your capacity to adapt, accept and learn on an emotional level. How much you seek comfort, relinquish control and worry about things you can't changed.
